main event: An observer reported sighting a luminous object in the sky in Kaysville, Kentucky, on February 5, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as brighter than the North Star and appeared to change its course by about 30 degrees towards the ENE., The object had an elevation of about 25 degrees initially., Witness was a deputy sheriff., The sighting lasted approximately 5 minutes., The object was reported to have a round shape and gave off a steady, bright light.
sighted object: a bright, luminous object in the sky
witness description: Deputy Sheriff for Maysville Police Dept.
